definition.value: A halomethane that is chloromethane in which one of the hydrogens has been replaced by a bromine atom.
A thiomorpholinemonocarboxylic acid having the carboxy group at the 3-position.
An optically active form of asparagine having L-configuration.
A member of the class of furans that is furan in which the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a hexyl group.
A glycerone 3-phosphate having an unspecified O-alkyl substituent at the 1-position.
